{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:14:11.860230+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's a comprehensive summary of how to run, build, and preview this React admin app:\n\n---\n\n## 📦 Tech Stack\n\n**Vite + React 18 + TypeScript + MUI (Material UI)**\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 Running Locally (Development)\n\n### 1. One-time Setup (using Taskfile)\n```bash\n# Install task runner (if not already installed): https://taskfile.dev/\ntask init\n```\nThis will:\n- Install global tools (`conventional-changelog-cli`, `standard-version`, `commitizen`)\n- Copy `envs/.env.local` → `.env`\n- Run `yarn install`\n\n### 2. Start the Dev Server\n```bash\nyarn dev\n```\n- Sets `NODE_ENV=local` via `cross-env`\n- Starts Vite dev server with `--host` (accessible on LAN)\n- **Default port:** `10086` (configured in `envs/.env.local`)\n- **API base URL:** `https://mock.local.lantron.ltd`\n- **HMR:** WebSocket on `localhost:10086`\n\n### Manual alternative (without Taskfile)\n```bash\ncp envs/.env.local .env\nyarn install\nyarn dev\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🏗️ Building for Different Environments\n\nThe app uses **per-environment `.env` files** in the `envs/` directory, loaded by Vite based on the mode flag.\n\n| Command | Env File | Vite Mode | Target |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `yarn build` | (default/prod) | `prod` | Production |\n| `yarn build:prod` | `envs/.env.prod` | `production` | Production (explicit) |\n| `yarn build:stg` | `envs/.env.stg` | `test` | Staging |\n| `yarn dev:stg` | `envs/.env.stg` | — | Staging dev server |\n\nAll builds output to the `dist/` directory.\n\n---\n\n## 👀 Previewing a Production Build\n\nAfter building, serve the static output locally:\n```bash\nyarn serve\n```\nThis runs `vite preview --host` to serve the contents of `dist/` with LAN access.\n\n---\n\n## 🐳 Docker Build & Serve\n\nThe `Dockerfile` uses a **multi-stage build**:\n1. **Build stage** (`node:lts-alpine`): Runs `yarn` then `yarn build` to produce `dist/`.\n2. **Serve stage** (`nginx:alpine`): Copies `dist/` and `nginx.conf` into the Nginx web root and exposes **port 80**.\n\n```bash\ndocker build -t vite-react-admin .\ndocker run -p 8080:80 vite-react-admin\n```\nThen open `http://localhost:8080`.\n\n---\n\n## 🌐 Environment Variables\n\nEach `.env` file in `envs/` defines:\n\n| Variable | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `NODE_ENV` | Environment label (`local`, `stg`, `prod`) |\n| `VITE_BUILD_ENV` | Build environment (`development` / `production`) |\n| `VITE_HOST` | Target hostname |\n| `VITE_PORT` | Dev server port |\n| `VITE_BASE_URL` | Public base path (`./`) |\n| `VITE_OUTPUT_DIR` | Build output directory (`dist`) |\n| `VITE_APP_BASE_API` | Backend API base URL (mock server) |\n\n---\n\n## 📋 Quick Reference\n\n| Action | Command |\n|---|---|\n| Full init | `task init` |\n| Local dev | `yarn dev` |\n| Staging dev | `yarn dev:stg` |\n| Build (prod) | `yarn build:prod` |\n| Build (staging) | `yarn build:stg` |\n| Preview build | `yarn serve` |\n| Lint | `yarn lint` |\n| Auto-fix lint | `yarn fix` |\n| Docker | `docker build -t app . && docker run -p 8080:80 app` |", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 924, "prompt_tokens": 8042, "total_tokens": 8966, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 23, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 7488, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0010718268, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002679468, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00080388}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780863236-euAuDzLTw5z28gRDgC3a", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3b8-7817-7cc2-8ac2-ca2cc0e796c1-0", "tool_calls": 